Former Governor of Akwa Ibom and a presidential hopeful of the All Progressives Congress, Godswill Akpabio has denied dropping out of the 2023 presidential race. There were rumours in the media that the former Minister of Niger Delta dropped his ambition for former Governor of Lagos, Bola Tinubu. Also Read: APC Primary: Umahi Did Not Step Down For Lawan, Says Aide However, the former lawmaker took to twitter on Sunday to deny the rumour. He appealed to the national delegates of the party to disregard, what he described as ‘wicked lies,’ stating that he won’t withdraw from the race. See his tweet below: … behind my aspiration. I will not withdraw because I have your support. Together, we will triumph and I will emerge the presidential candidate of our great party and we will march together to win the presidential election. — Godswill Obot Akpabio, CON (@Senator_Akpabio) June 5, 2022 